  "text": "In this experiment, we compare performance based on the number of state transmissions due to the trigger γ noise in [CITATION_1] . In particular, we compare different choices off in Equation (12): approach. The first plot shows the stochastic trajectory of the system in red and our method in blue. Every jump corresponds to communication due to noise effects. The local model is updated when the horizontal line is crossed. In the second plot we an improvement in communication savings compared to the send-on-delta protocol, which is highlighted by zooming in. Furthermore, we show in the third plot similar performance with respect to the analytical model, with the addition benefit of significantly reducing the model complexity.",
